  m_Name: Common_calcaneal_tendon.L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Common_calcaneal_tendon.L
  partName: Common calcaneal tendon Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The common calcaneal tendons are strong connective structures positioned along
    the posterior aspect of both hindlimbs, attaching to the calcaneus. Formed by
    contributions from the gastrocnemius, superficial digital flexor, and biceps
    femoris, they enable powerful hock extension essential
  - for walking, running, jumping, and posture maintenance. These tendons also facilitate
    energy transfer and shock absorption during locomotion. Due to high mechanical
    stress, structural integrity is critical. Injury or rupture causes severe lameness,
    instability, and impaired hindlimb performance.
